    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Officials charged with attending fairs and markets to carry out any or all of the following duties: to regulate the standard of weights and measures, to punish misdemeanors, to collect market dues, and to inspect the items displayed at the market. Typically relevant in historical contexts.</Note_Text>
